# Network Security Basics (After TCP/IP)

After learning how data moves, the next step is learning how to protect it.

---

## Security Controls

- Firewall – filters network traffic based on rules  
- IDS – detects suspicious activity  
- IPS – detects and blocks attacks  
- VPN – creates secure encrypted connection  

---

## Common Network Attacks

- MitM (Man-in-the-Middle) – intercepts communication  
- DDoS – overwhelms system with traffic  
- Packet Sniffing – captures network data  

---

## CIA Triad (Core Security Model)

- Confidentiality – protect data (encryption)  
- Integrity – ensure data is not changed (hashing)  
- Availability – keep systems accessible (backup, redundancy)  

---

## Cryptography Basics

- Symmetric Encryption – one key (encrypt + decrypt)  
- Asymmetric Encryption – public + private keys  
- Hashing – fixed output for data verification  

---

## Key Idea

- Learn how systems are attacked  
- Learn how to defend them  
- Apply security at every layer  

---
